social_posts.post_text:
Iceland - Day 1
Arrival, exploring Reykjavik, food tour, sky lagoon.

Iceland Day 2
Exploring the island nature and waterfalls, relaxing end at the blue lagoon. #iceland

London day 1 and 2.

The Mall, Buckingham Palace, Coronation Decorations, City Exploration, National Gallery, Beyond the Streets Exhibit and Abba Voyage.

London Day 3 and 4
Tower of London, Tate Modern, Millennium Bridge, St. Paul’s Cathedral, Cabaret, Kensington Palace, Harry Potter and the Cursed Child.

social_posts.post_text: Thin Air Exhibit, Westminster Abbey, Design Museum, Royal Ballet.
Still in disbelief I got to attend the Eurovision final this year, great hosting by Liverpool. Hope to do it again next year! #eurovision
Liverpool was compact and easy to explore the people were so proud of their city. Amazing weather during Eurovision weekend. #eurovision
Arrived to Rome from Liverpool, walked the city center that evening, did a big walking tour the next day learning a lot of Roman history and seeing the mayor historical sites. #rome #travel
I could spent months exploring this city. #rome #romeitaly
Probably should have started my trip with this amazing food tour, great to walk around the city and learn about the people, their custom and food. #rome #romeitaly

Posting my Milan adventure a month after the trip 😅
Lovely trip from Rome and amazing shopping experience at Prada.
Last days in Milan and end of my spring europe trip. Loved Milan.
Quick weekend trip to San Diego to watch @heathermcdonald juicy comedy show. Lovely town really fell in love with the chill vibes and beautiful beaches.

Madrid - Day 1

* Early arrival in the city.
* Tour of El Prado museum. 
* Venezuelan lunch. 
* El Retiro park. 
* Evening out.

Madrid - Day 2

* Royal Palace Tour.
* Almudena Church. 
* Plaza Mayor. 
* Tapas. 
* Walking tour with @olivamarquez .
* Tablao Flamenco 1911.

Madrid - Day 3

* Rainy day.
* Museo Nacional Thyssen-Bornemisza. 
* Museo Reina Sofía. 
* Casa Loewe Madrid.
* Tablao Cardamomo.

Barcelona - Day 1

* Sagrada familia park. 
* Palau de la Musica Catalana
* Moco Museum Barcelona
* The Barcelona Cathedral
* Ciutadella Park.
* Dinner with @nuthinking

Barcelona - Day 2

* Walking tour of the city.

Day dedicated to architecture and mostly Gaudí. 

- Casa Batlló
- Casa Loewe
- Casa Milà
- Casa Vicens

Exploring museums and architecture in Barcelona.

- Joan Miró Foundation
- Museu Nacional d’Art de Catalunya
- Poble Espanyol
- Mies van der Rohe Pavilion

Last day in Barcelona, started the day with a visit to the Picasso museum, quick train ride to Sitges for some beach time with friends and back to Barcelona for @granhoteldelasreinas a perfect conclusion to my time in Spain.
Fell in love with Lisbon right upon arrival. Amazing food in a bohemian city.
Second day in Lisbon a full day of adventures starting with a half day walking tour learning about the history of Portugal, great food, architectural landmarks and some nightlife.
Day trip to Sintra to explore beautiful castles, Portuguese towns, the most occidental point in Europe, and enjoy a Fado show.
Last day in Portugal a full day of adventures and explorations. I’ll be back 👏
First day in Geneva best highlight was walking around the lake and admiring the clear water, great restaurants and high-end shopping. Lots of beautiful parks and spaces to explore too.
Museums, United Nations, Red Cross Museum and more lake walks on day 2 of exploring Geneva.
